                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                              Ethiopic bookbinding with wooden boards and a plain textile chemise, preserved in its slip case.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Boards">
                              The upper board is broken in two halves held togheter by loops of thread passing through the holes done into the boards.
                              A fracture is forming on the lower board.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              Chemise in plain white cloth. A strip of red fabric lined with white fabric is sewn to the headcap and it extends in order to cover the three edges of the codex.
                              Both ends of the strip are decorated with colorful embroidery.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing is damaged and repaired with different kinds of threads so it is not possible to identify the original pattern.
                              The original sewing thread seems to be of <term key="animalThread" ana="#animalThread">animal origin</term>.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b9" type="Spine">
                              Small holes are present close to the head and tail of the quires, prabably remains of the tackets.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b11" type="EndLeaves">
                              The first quire has a protective function.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b12" type="SlipCase">
                              The codex is preserved in its two-part slip case made of stiff leather.
                            </decoNote>
                          </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
